      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Earnest money goes into escrow because it acts as a good-faith deposit, not an immediate payment to the seller. The escrow account is a neutral third-party holding place, which keeps the funds safe until all the terms of the contract are met. If the deal falls through for a specific reason, the escrow agent manages the return or distribution of those funds according to the contract. This process protects both the buyer and the seller from disputes.",
